name: Fedelm of Munster

attributes.attribute: Fairy caretaker of the future king of Cashel
marked by fire during a ritual celebrated by Fedelm and her sisters
related name seen in an early Celtic inscription found in a woman’s grave that describes a college of sorceresses or seers

sources: Monaghan, Patricia. The Encyclopedia of Celtic Mythology and Folklore. Checkmark Books, 2008.
text: Fedelm, the Fairy in charge of taking care of the future monarch of Cashel, Corc Mac Luigthic, had performed a rite with her siblings that caused the latter to be identified by fire. Some believe that the name Fedelm could have referred to a typical name given to female fortune tellers, and there is evidence to support this claim. For example, there is an ancient Celtic inscription that mentions a group of witches or prophets that goes by the name of Gaulish Uidula, which was discovered in a woman's grave. Despite the tough interpretation of the text, it seems to allude to a group of magical women who were connected in some way.
